\par \pard \ql \li0\ri0 \sb120 \fi360 2. The Voluntary Plan
\par \pard \ql \li0\ri0 \sb120 \fi360 The Board insists upon the implementation of an all voluntary plan for desegregation. Such plans do not, however, provide meaningful desegregation. A voluntary plan was struck down by this Court in Green v. County School Board of New Kent County, 391 U.S. 430, 440-441 (1968). Lower federal courts have consistently struck them down. n3 
\par \pard 
\par \fs16 \pard \ql \li600\ri0 \sb120 \fi360 n3 See, e.g.  Hall v. St. Helena Parish School Board, 417 F.2d 801, 807 (5th Cir. 1969), cert. denied, 396 U.S. 904 (1969); Davis v. Board of School Commissioners of Mobile County, 430 F.2d 883 & 889 (5th Cir. 1970), aff'd, 402 U.S. 33, 37 (1971); Kelly v. Guinn, 456 F.2d 100, 108-109 (9th Cir. 1972, cert. denied, 413 U.S. 919 (1973).
\par \fs20 \pard \ql \li0\ri0 \sb120 \fi360 A review of the school board's voluntary plan demonstrates that this plan, like all voluntary plans, is insufficient as a tool for desegregation unless mandatory provisions act as a supplement to the program. The school board's plan relies heavily on two programs,  \b \i0 \ul0 [*16]\b0 \i0 \ul0   Permits With Transportation (PWT) and Magnet schools. PWT allows students who choose to do so to attend a different school from the one that is in the neighborhoods. The magnet program creates certain schools which because of their asserted uniqueness, are designed to attract students.
\par \pard \ql \li0\ri0 \sb120 \fi360 After considering the evidence the trial court concluded that the Magnet program was ineffective in achieving desegregation. "Both the district and the experts... are unanimous that it is unlikely that any minority segregated schools in Los Angeles will be desegregated by the use of magnets and that the use of magnets cannot desegregate the district." Superior Court Opinion, Findings and Conclusions dated July 7, 1980 at 23, C.T. 17470. More importantly, however, is the fact that "the initial magnet program's success, if any there was, has been attributed to the threat of mandatory assignment..." Id. The total ineffectiveness of the magnet program is reflected in the statistics for the following schools: 
